3
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:09,780
It's been a while, Chief.

4
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:19,120
Eight years ago, he assaulted
government officials in Water Seven:

5
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,120
the fugitive Cutty Flam.

6
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:27,590
And the criminal responsible for an attack
on Marine battleships at Ohara in the West Blue:

7
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:29,170
Nico Robin.

8
00:02:29,170 --> 00:02:32,010
We've brought them here without a hitch.

9
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:35,090
Both are behind those doors.

10
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:37,550
Welcome back,

11
00:02:37,890 --> 00:02:41,640
Lucci, Kaku, Blueno, and Kalifa!

12
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:42,930
That's sexual harassment.

13
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:44,890
Just from saying your name?!

14
00:02:48,860 --> 00:02:51,610
Long time no see, Lucci.

15
00:02:51,610 --> 00:02:54,650
I see you look more arrogant than ever.

16
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:58,070
And I see you look dumber than ever, Jabra.

17
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:00,490
What'd you say?

18
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:03,580
Hold your horses.

19
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:05,790
We just got back.

20
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:11,920
He is correct. The two of you
must desist at once!

21
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:19,970
After all, this is a reunion
five years in the making!

22
00:03:39,530 --> 00:03:40,160
Ow...!

23
00:03:41,620 --> 00:03:44,950
Leave it to Fukuro to test us right away.

24
00:03:45,830 --> 00:03:48,790
Six Powers: Assessment!

25
00:03:49,380 --> 00:03:53,960
Suppose an armed guard
has a power level of ten.

26
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,840
I will now reveal...

27
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:58,630
your power levels.

28
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:00,720
I will uncover your strengths.

29
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:04,020
First, Kalifa: Power level 630.

30
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:06,850
Blueno: Power level 820.

31
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:09,770
Kaku: Power level 2,200.

32
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:11,980
Lucci...

33
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,940
Power level 4,000!

34
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:20,110
You said 4,000?! Hey,
did you measure it properly?!

35
00:04:20,110 --> 00:04:22,370
No one has a power level that high!

36
00:04:22,370 --> 00:04:23,870
It's correct!

37
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:26,080
Everyone got stronger!

38
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:33,540
I already measured Jabra's and Kumadori's,
so now I know how we rank among ourselves.

39
00:04:39,340 --> 00:04:41,260
Hey, Fukuro! Objection!

40
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:45,520
Lucci's one thing, but how the hell
am I weaker than Kaku?!

41
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:49,690
Kaku got stronger too!

42
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:53,520
Hey, don't let it go to your head, Kaku!

43
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:56,650
The assessment skill just
measures raw strength.

44
00:04:57,240 --> 00:05:00,490
In an actual fight,
I'd also have devil fruit powers.

45
00:05:00,490 --> 00:05:03,370
Don't go thinking you could ever beat me!

46
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:05,120
Think whatever you like.

47
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,000
I don't give a rat's ass about that stuff.

48
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,500
Well said.

49
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:12,080
Don't lend your ears to a stray dog.

50
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:18,550
What do you mean, "stray dog," Lucci?!
You mangy monster cat!

51
00:05:26,850 --> 00:05:29,230
Hey, stop it, both of you!

52
00:05:29,230 --> 00:05:33,810
Is it just me, or is Jabra
a bit touchier than usual?

53
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:36,270
Every guard on the island is talking about

54
00:05:36,270 --> 00:05:41,490
how Jabra got rejected
by the waitress Gatherine yesterday.

55
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:42,860
That explains it.

56
00:05:42,860 --> 00:05:44,570
H-Hey, hold on a sec!

57
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:46,950
How does everyone know about that?!

58
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:50,040
I blabbed about it to the guards
on the main island.

59
00:05:51,710 --> 00:05:52,920
It was you!

60
00:05:56,880 --> 00:06:02,170
Oh, please! This is only an issue because you
started with all that ranking nonsense!

61
00:06:02,170 --> 00:06:08,890
Having mastered the Six Powers,
you have all far surpassed ordinary people.

62
00:06:08,890 --> 00:06:12,100
Isn't a power level of 500 enough
to give you superhuman status?

63
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:16,560
Chief: Power level nine.
Less than one armed guard.

64
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:20,990
Zip it, you! As your chief,
it shouldn't matter anyway!

65
00:06:20,990 --> 00:06:24,320
Besides, did you forget
about my special sword?!

66
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:27,450
I've always known that you've
lacked certain attributes, Chief.

67
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:33,370
H-H-H-Hey! You shouldn't be so blunt, Kalifa.

68
00:06:33,370 --> 00:06:34,460
That's sexual harassment.

69
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:36,920
What?! Just by responding?!

70
00:06:38,590 --> 00:06:39,300
Chief...

71
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,340
Wh-What is it?

72
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,550
That's sexual harassment!

73
00:06:43,550 --> 00:06:44,550
Just existing?!

74
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:50,470
Kalifa! How rude of you!

75
00:06:51,350 --> 00:06:58,060
Chief! A-Allow me to take responsibility
and commit ritual suicide immediately!

76
00:06:58,060 --> 00:06:59,690
Seppuku!

77
00:06:59,690 --> 00:07:00,900
Iron Body.

78
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:05,610
For shame... I cannot die.

79
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:07,820
Hurry up and die already!

80
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:14,580
Anyway, you all performed spectacularly
over the past five years.

81
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,330
Oh, I almost forgot.

82
00:07:16,330 --> 00:07:19,420
This isn't really a reward
for your efforts or anything,

83
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:21,590
but I do have something I want to give you.

84
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:25,090
Well, I'll do that later.

85
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:28,090
In any case, I'd like to meet...

86
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:31,850
the "hope" of the entire world!

87
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:44,690
Go in already!

88
00:07:47,410 --> 00:07:48,820
You too!

89
00:08:01,670 --> 00:08:03,460
I'm just so excited!

90
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:07,930
I'm surprised to see you survived
that accident eight years ago,

91
00:08:08,340 --> 00:08:09,930
Cutty Flam.

92
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:11,430
There's also...

93
00:08:11,430 --> 00:08:15,180
one of the world's most dangerous,
most wanted women:

94
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,230
Nico Robin!

95
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:20,560
I feel fantastic! However...

96
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:23,190
it's unfortunate that
the world's citizens don't know

97
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:27,320
about the true value and magnitude
of the work accomplished today.

98
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:29,320
It'll be several years...

99
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:34,490
before anything about today
even comes to light.

100
00:08:35,660 --> 00:08:40,790
I believe the justice doled out by those
old government geezers is too lenient!

101
00:08:41,130 --> 00:08:44,130
Only through sacrifice
will we achieve our goal.

102
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:48,510
Our hard work will ensure peace
for all of humanity.

103
00:08:49,970 --> 00:08:57,100
Killing some of the fools standing in our way
is a small sacrifice for world peace.

104
00:08:57,430 --> 00:09:02,270
Fools like that fishman, who refused
to hand over a certain something.

105
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:07,070
As a rebel against justice,
of course he deserved death.

106
00:09:10,740 --> 00:09:12,990
He definitely deserved it!

107
00:09:14,530 --> 00:09:16,120
You're insane!

108
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:18,870
Mr. Tom lost his life
protecting those blueprints!

109
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:22,500
He died because of idiots like you!

110
00:09:27,420 --> 00:09:31,010
Wh-What're you doing?!
Help me, guys! Hey!

111
00:09:32,430 --> 00:09:35,350
Ow, ow! Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow! Ow!

112
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,390
Kumadori!

113
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:43,980
Roger!

114
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,770
Hurry up and help me, hey! Hey!

115
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:50,900
Now... now... now...!

116
00:10:10,170 --> 00:10:11,800
Gum-Gum...

117
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,010
Gatling!

118
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:15,390
Gum-Gum...

119
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:17,810
Whip!

120
00:10:20,180 --> 00:10:21,930
Giant Scythe!

121
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:25,770
Bell!

122
00:10:27,230 --> 00:10:29,150
Mallet!

123
00:10:30,650 --> 00:10:32,780
Bazooka!

124
00:10:38,530 --> 00:10:39,950
Gum-Gum...

125
00:10:39,950 --> 00:10:40,910
Stamp!

126
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:46,290
Chief, main island reporting!

127
00:10:46,290 --> 00:10:49,460
Chief Spandam! Please respond!

128
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,550
It's no use! I can't get through!

129
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:54,220
Is his receiver off the hook again...?

130
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,680
Not now!

131
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:58,390
Seriously, not at a critical time like this!

132
00:10:58,890 --> 00:11:01,350
Hey, where did Straw Hat go?

133
00:11:01,350 --> 00:11:03,060
He's right beneath you!

134
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:04,940
What?! Right beneath us?!

135
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:09,690
Get him already!

136
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:11,570
There! Down there!

137
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:12,900
Dammit! Boxed in!

138
00:11:20,370 --> 00:11:22,700
Gum-Gum...

139
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:24,960
Volcano!

140
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:53,900
Th... The wall...! The wall is falling!

141
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:56,320
Get clear!

142
00:11:59,450 --> 00:12:02,240
Gum-Gum...

143
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:06,370
Gatling!

144
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:08,580
Watch out!

145
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:16,090
Chief Spandam! Please come in!

146
00:12:16,090 --> 00:12:19,890
We need a plan of action!
We can't stop Straw Hat Luffy!

147
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:24,010
Straw Hat Luffy is headed to the courthouse!

148
00:12:24,010 --> 00:12:25,890
Tighten our defenses! On the double!

149
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:27,600
Be quiet!

150
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:29,140
What's this ruckus?!

151
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:31,810
You woke me up!

152
00:12:31,810 --> 00:12:33,730
Ch-Chief Justice!

153
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:37,360
That's right! Lest you forget,

154
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:40,240
I am the chief justice of Enies Lobby!

155
00:12:40,570 --> 00:12:44,240
On the left, I am the Left Baskerville!

156
00:12:44,990 --> 00:12:49,210
On the right, I am the Right Baskerville!

157
00:12:49,210 --> 00:12:52,250
And in the center, it is I,

158
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:54,130
Central Freeway!

159
00:12:54,130 --> 00:12:55,340
– Say what?!
– Say what?!

160
00:12:55,710 --> 00:12:57,550
Ch-Chief Justice!

161
00:12:57,550 --> 00:13:00,970
A pirate is going on a rampage
on the main island,

162
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:04,600
but the men are saying they can't
get in touch with Chief Spandam.

163
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,930
Please assume command!

164
00:13:06,310 --> 00:13:09,440
A pirate, you say. Pirates are guilty!

165
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:15,820
Oh, come on. Let him off with a warning.

166
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:19,490
Then, let's compromise and give him...

167
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:20,820
the death penalty!

168
00:13:20,820 --> 00:13:22,200
– Say what?!
– Say what?!

169
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:26,580
There's trouble, Chief Justice!

170
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:30,960
We got a report that Straw Hat's comrades
took out Kashi at the island gate...

171
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,960
and that Oimo is losing too!

172
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:35,750
– What?! Don't let them breach the gate!
– What?! Don't let them breach the gate!

173
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:40,970
– Send 100 watchdogs immediately!
– Send 100 watchdogs immediately!

174
00:13:40,970 --> 00:13:42,090
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

175
00:13:46,310 --> 00:13:49,350
Dammit! The five minutes are over!

176
00:13:49,350 --> 00:13:53,020
This is bad! Hurry up
and clear the path for Rocketman!

177
00:13:53,020 --> 00:13:55,480
You aren't passing through this gate!

178
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,070
We got the gate unlocked!

179
00:13:59,070 --> 00:14:01,150
Now we gotta push open the doors!

180
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:02,780
What?! Ah, crud!

181
00:14:02,780 --> 00:14:04,030
Alright! Good going!

182
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:05,780
Go!

183
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:09,080
No one's touching this gate!

184
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:11,250
Rope Action...

185
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:14,170
Top Knot!

186
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:15,580
Take this!

187
00:14:17,540 --> 00:14:20,510
Whoa! That's a Galley-La foreman, alright!

188
00:14:20,510 --> 00:14:23,630
What?! This puny rope...

189
00:14:24,470 --> 00:14:26,680
Franky Family! Pull!

190
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:27,930
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

191
00:14:28,810 --> 00:14:32,180
Just leave it to us! Let's go,
Sodom and Gomorrah! Grab the rope!

192
00:14:40,030 --> 00:14:42,530
Charge into the gate!

193
00:14:43,570 --> 00:14:47,280
H-Hey! Hold on! Oimo's feeling dizzy!

194
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:49,490
Push the doors!

195
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:56,880
Look! The doors...!

196
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,170
The doors are opening!

197
00:14:58,790 --> 00:15:00,590
What happened to Oimo?!

198
00:15:01,090 --> 00:15:02,550
Just a little more!

199
00:15:14,810 --> 00:15:17,560
They're through the gate!

200
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:26,740
H-H-H-Hey! Hey!

201
00:15:27,490 --> 00:15:28,530
Hey...

202
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:34,790
Is that... a sea train?

203
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:36,250
What's going on?

204
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:53,720
What?! It's rushing straight toward us!

205
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:57,060
They're really gonna launch
onto the main island!

206
00:15:57,060 --> 00:16:01,020
No way! They can't jump over that iron fence!

207
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:06,320
Get a move on! Don't let them charge in!

208
00:16:06,950 --> 00:16:08,950
Close the gate!

209
00:16:19,370 --> 00:16:20,630
Hey, granny!

210
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:22,040
Huh? What's up?

211
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,590
Change of plans!

212
00:16:23,590 --> 00:16:26,130
Guys, looks like we're changing our plan.

213
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:30,340
The samurai man says everyone
needs to hold on tight to something.

214
00:16:30,340 --> 00:16:32,550
"Hold on tight"?!

215
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:35,560
Hey, Swordsmoron! What's the big idea?!

216
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:38,480
They closed the main gate.

217
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,020
They what?!

218
00:16:40,020 --> 00:16:42,810
What?! This is terrible!
We're gonna crash into the gate!

219
00:16:42,810 --> 00:16:44,440
What'll we do?! What'll we do?!

220
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,940
Break away, Kokoro!

221
00:16:45,030 --> 00:16:46,940
What'll we do?! What'll we do?!

222
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:50,320
Don't worry.

223
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:51,490
There's a way.

224
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,710
Push that fence, frog!

225
00:16:58,710 --> 00:17:00,580
– What?!
– What?!

226
00:17:25,770 --> 00:17:27,150
He can't...!

227
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:30,200
Any farther and we'll
run aground on the iron fence!

228
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:41,540
No way!

229
00:17:42,170 --> 00:17:43,670
The sea train...

230
00:17:43,670 --> 00:17:46,000
...is flying!

231
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,010
No! We're gonna die!

232
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:51,510
What?! We're gonna die?!

233
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:55,430
Nami, hurry into my arms!

234
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:58,470
We're gonna land in that gaping hole, you idiot!

235
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:06,820
Zoro! You've figured out our landing, right?!

236
00:18:09,530 --> 00:18:11,030
Just leave it to...

237
00:18:19,290 --> 00:18:20,120
luck.

238
00:18:20,950 --> 00:18:23,170
– It's up to luck?!
– It's up to luck?!

239
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:31,760
Oimo is down!

240
00:18:50,110 --> 00:18:53,200
A-Are you... the Straw Hats?!

241
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,200
That's right!

242
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,450
– We are?!
– We are?!

243
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:59,660
Whatever. It doesn't matter.

244
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:01,410
C'mon, shake a leg!

245
00:19:01,410 --> 00:19:06,580
All right, guys! Press on as far as we can go!

246
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:09,040
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

247
00:19:19,050 --> 00:19:20,600
Paulie!

248
00:19:21,220 --> 00:19:22,140
Dammit!

249
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,560
Who the hell are you?!

250
00:19:25,940 --> 00:19:28,690
We're Enies Lobby's elite guards,

251
00:19:28,690 --> 00:19:32,320
the Watchdogs of the Law,
Watchdogs for short!

252
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:36,030
Under orders from Chief Justice Baskerville,

253
00:19:36,030 --> 00:19:39,320
we'll cast judgment on you
and bring you down at this gate!

254
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:43,950
Dammit! They send one guard
after another to block us!

255
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:46,620
Oimo! What're you doing?!

256
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:50,130
How could you let
pirates like them open the gate?!

257
00:19:50,130 --> 00:19:50,750
Ow!

258
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:55,880
Oimo passed out!

259
00:19:57,840 --> 00:20:00,760
– Not good! He's up and at 'em!
– Not good! He's up and at 'em!

260
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,600
Oimo won't forgive you!

261
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:08,480
You're not gonna get away with this!

262
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:17,950
– What?!
– What?!

263
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:38,090
Wh-Why the hell did Rocketman...
come from the sky?!

264
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:41,010
– Opening the gates was pointless?!
– Opening the gates was pointless?!

265
00:20:49,390 --> 00:20:51,770
Wh-What just happened?!

266
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:55,940
Do you think they're okay
after crashing in like that?

267
00:21:01,780 --> 00:21:03,870
Th-They aren't coming out...

268
00:21:20,050 --> 00:21:22,010
Hey, what happened?!

269
00:21:25,390 --> 00:21:28,100
Wh-Who are those two?!

270
00:21:35,070 --> 00:21:36,360
Huh?

271
00:21:37,070 --> 00:21:39,110
Should we have introduced ourselves?

272
00:21:39,610 --> 00:21:42,110
That's stupid. Why should we have?

273
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:44,030
It's Roronoa's group!

274
00:21:44,030 --> 00:21:46,240
– It's about time!
– It's about time!

275
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:54,040
All according to plan...

276
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:55,500
Really?!

